UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1927
1 provide basic health and health-related services in accordance
2 with KRS 194A.700 to 194A.729; and
3 2. Assisted living services and, in accordance with federal law, shall not
4 include the cost of room and board.
5 (3) The cabinet shall, no later than ninety (90) days after receiving federal approval
6 for the waiver amendment application required in subsection (2) of this section,
7 promulgate administrative regulations in accordance with KRS Chapter 13A to
8 implement this section, including but not limited to:
9 (a) Provider qualifications;
10 (b) Reimbursement rates for assisted living services; and
11 (c) A maximum room and board rate that an assisted living community may
12 charge an HCB waiver participant.
13 (4) If the waiver amendment application required in subsection (2) of this section is
14 denied by the federal Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services, this section
15 shall have no force or effect.
16 Section 2. If the Cabinet for Health and Family Services or the Department for
17 Medicaid Services determines that a state plan amendment, waiver, or any other form of
18 authorization or approval from any federal agency to implement Section 1 of this Act is
19 necessary to prevent the loss of federal funds or to comply with federal law, the cabinet
20 or department:
21 (1) Shall, within 90 days after the effective date of this section, request the
22 necessary federal authorization or approval to implement Section 1 of this Act; and
23 (2) May only delay implementation of the provisions of Section 1 of this Act for
24 which federal authorization or approval was deemed necessary until the federal
25 authorization or approval is granted.
26 Section 3. Sections 1 and 2 of this Act shall constitute the specific authorization
27 required under KRS 205.5372(1).
